@node In general, Commandverview, Main, Main
@chapter In general

FileX has a nearly Commodore-Amiga-User-Interface-Style-Guide-conform ARexxport.

If no PORTNAME is given, the port will get the name 'FILEX'.
If a port with the same name allready exists, a number will be appended to the name that
will be increased until a non-existing portname is found (`NAME'->`NAME.1'->`NAME.2').

The argunents of the commands will be evaluated in the way AmigaDOS does.
If you don't know the different argument types, read this short list:

@table
@item <arg>
     A simple string. It's not necessary to specify the argument's name.
@item <arg>/S
     Switch. Will be set through declaring an argument.
@item <arg>/K
     Key word.  This argument must be given with an argument's name.
     (`<arg> = value' oder `<arg> value'.
@item <arg>/N
     Number.  This argument must be a decimal number.
@item <arg>/T
     Changing switch.  Through specification of this argument a value
     will change its condition.
@item <arg>/A
     This argument must be given.
@item <arg>/F
     The rest of the line will be understood as an argument, although if
     there are some more keywords
@item <arg>/M
     Serveral values are possible.
@end table

   For all commands that return something it's possible to set a
variable to the return value by specifing the name of it with the
argument VAR.  The same applies to the argument STEM and its
stemvariables.

All commands with an argument ID return rc = 5 if the ID is invalid.
If no ID is given, the command wil use the current view, window or file.

